The paper proposes a domain-specific language for building generators for property-based random testing, which is a technique commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE). The language focuses on expressing generators through annotations on logical predicates, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the formal semantics of the language, which is related to logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper evaluates the language on examples from the property-based testing literature, which is related to formal methods (cs.FL) and machine learning (cs.LG) since property-based testing can be seen as a form of automated testing and machine learning can be used to improve the efficiency of testing.
